WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
[lively music]

00:04.437 --> 00:12.345
♪ ♪

00:12.412 --> 00:14.481
♪ Harvey ♪

00:16.416 --> 00:18.351
♪ Harvey ♪

00:24.324 --> 00:26.893
♪ Harvey ♪

00:33.366 --> 00:35.902
Well, boys, according to
the GPS on my smart phone,

00:35.969 --> 00:37.470
we're making good time.

00:37.537 --> 00:39.973
Is everyone excited
to see the comet tonight?

00:40.039 --> 00:41.441
- Yes, Dad.
- Yes, Mr. Beaks!

00:41.508 --> 00:43.777
Does anyone need to stop
and make a wee-wee?

00:43.843 --> 00:45.645
{\an1}[all]
No, Mr. Beaks.

00:45.712 --> 00:47.046
[laughs]
Great!

00:47.113 --> 00:48.448
{\an3}Harvey, it's really nice
of your dad

00:48.515 --> 00:50.250
{\an3}to take us all camping
like this.

00:50.316 --> 00:52.919
{\an3}Your dad is nice.
I like him.

00:52.986 --> 00:55.555
{\an1}I like him, too.
You want to see something cool?

00:55.622 --> 00:56.790
Check this out.

00:56.856 --> 00:58.558
{\an1}It's a picture
of my dad and his dad,

00:58.625 --> 00:59.759
my grandpa,

00:59.826 --> 01:01.428
{\an1}from the last time
the comet came through

01:01.494 --> 01:02.762
25 years ago.

01:02.829 --> 01:04.330
Why aren't you
in the picture?

01:05.465 --> 01:07.600
- I wasn't born yet.
- Oh.

01:07.667 --> 01:09.335
Harvey, come here, buddy.

01:09.402 --> 01:10.770
Are you looking at
that picture again?

01:10.837 --> 01:12.605
- Maybe.
- [sighs]

01:12.672 --> 01:14.140
{\an3}You know, seeing that
comet with my dad

01:14.207 --> 01:15.842
{\an3}is something
I'll remember forever.

01:15.909 --> 01:18.478
I can't believe I get to
share this with you, too.

01:18.545 --> 01:20.146
[blubbering]

01:20.213 --> 01:23.116
{\an3}Oh, boy, here come
the waterworks.

01:23.183 --> 01:27.020
It's okay, Dad.
Cool guys cry sometimes.

01:27.086 --> 01:28.888
{\an1}Guys, I need
to ask you something,

01:28.955 --> 01:30.390
and I need an honest answer.

01:30.457 --> 01:32.792
How jealous am I making you
right now?

01:32.859 --> 01:35.495
[techno music]

01:35.562 --> 01:41.434
♪ ♪

01:41.501 --> 01:44.237
Looks like we found a great
place to break for dinner.

01:44.304 --> 01:45.572
OK, it's 7:00 now.

01:45.638 --> 01:48.408
{\an1}We eat dinner and be back
on the trail by 7:30.

01:48.475 --> 01:49.876
By 3:00 a.m.,

01:49.943 --> 01:53.780
we're having the best Harvey-Dad
moment time ever!

01:53.847 --> 01:58.718
♪ ♪

02:03.823 --> 02:05.492
[fire crackling]

02:05.558 --> 02:07.794
{\an3}Check out my new
titanium skewer, huh?

02:07.861 --> 02:09.529
{\an3}Roast two s'mores
at once.

02:10.797 --> 02:12.098
Eh, oh...

02:12.165 --> 02:14.200
All right, fellas,

02:14.267 --> 02:16.936
{\an3}before we get back
on the old dusty trail,

02:17.003 --> 02:18.938
{\an3}who wants to hear
a ghost story?

02:19.005 --> 02:21.641
(all)
Ah! We! Yeah! I do! I do!

02:21.708 --> 02:24.010
{\an3}Let's set the mood,
shall we?

02:24.077 --> 02:26.079
♪ ♪

02:26.145 --> 02:28.648
Once there was
this camper,

02:28.715 --> 02:33.052
and he was camping
right here on this very spot.

02:33.119 --> 02:36.656
And he was cooking
marshmallows

02:36.723 --> 02:37.857
just like we are.

02:37.924 --> 02:40.293
Ooh! And it burned.

02:40.360 --> 02:43.630
But he ate the burned...
marshmallow anyways.

02:43.696 --> 02:46.366
And it screwed him up
big time.

02:46.432 --> 02:49.302
And it--and it turned him
i-into a monster.

02:49.369 --> 02:52.972
And he just started
eating children!

02:53.039 --> 02:55.041
Aah! Why would he do that?

02:55.108 --> 02:57.577
Because monsters
aren't rational.

02:57.644 --> 02:59.379
Oh, my crud!

02:59.445 --> 03:01.114
Wait, I think I heard
something.

03:01.180 --> 03:03.116
I better go
check it out.

03:03.182 --> 03:05.084
He'll be fine.

03:05.151 --> 03:07.153
The monsters only
eat kids, right?

03:09.455 --> 03:11.057
[roaring]

03:11.124 --> 03:12.892
[all scream]

03:12.959 --> 03:13.993
[roaring]

03:14.060 --> 03:15.495
Ha ha.
Just kidding, boys.

03:15.562 --> 03:17.063
Just--ow!

03:17.130 --> 03:18.064
[all screaming]

03:18.131 --> 03:20.633
Ow! No, wait, wait!

03:20.700 --> 03:23.736
Whoa! Ow! Ow!

03:23.803 --> 03:26.272
[grunting]

03:26.339 --> 03:28.942
Wait, it's not
a monster.

03:29.008 --> 03:30.476
That's my dad!

03:30.543 --> 03:34.113
{\an1}Miriam, try these
gravel and molasses truffles.

03:34.180 --> 03:35.548
Dad, are you okay?

03:35.615 --> 03:38.451
{\an1}Don't worry, boys.
I'm perfectly capable of...

03:38.518 --> 03:40.186
[thud]

03:40.253 --> 03:42.055
Yeah, he's pretty messed up.

03:42.121 --> 03:44.691
{\an3}Lucky for you people,
I know what to do.

03:44.757 --> 03:46.359
I was never here.

03:46.426 --> 03:48.061
You guys are in
so much trouble!

03:48.127 --> 03:49.629
Ahh! Ahh!

03:49.696 --> 03:51.030
Dade, what the heck?

03:51.097 --> 03:53.232
{\an1}Okay, okay,
whenever dad gets hurt,

03:53.299 --> 03:54.634
I just call Mom.

03:54.701 --> 03:56.936
[dialing, ringing]

03:57.003 --> 03:58.605
Mom, it's Dad. He's hurt--

03:58.671 --> 03:59.606
[muted screaming]

03:59.672 --> 04:00.907
Wait, Jeremy?

04:00.974 --> 04:03.343
Yes, Beaks Residence.
Everything is fine.

04:03.409 --> 04:05.912
Baby's fine.
Oh, no! Ahh!

04:05.979 --> 04:08.114
I hate bats! Ahh!

04:08.181 --> 04:10.283
I guess my mom's not there.

04:10.350 --> 04:12.852
So, what are we doing,
Harv-man, going home?

04:12.919 --> 04:14.621
Uh, well...

04:14.687 --> 04:16.389
(Irving voiceover)
You know, seeing that comet

04:16.456 --> 04:18.524
with my dad is something I'll
remember forever.

04:18.591 --> 04:22.362
This comet only comes
every 25 years.

04:22.428 --> 04:24.497
We're going to keep going.

04:24.564 --> 04:27.033
Okay, guys, we're going
to have to keep speed-walking

04:27.100 --> 04:29.636
if we're going to make it
to the field on time.

04:29.702 --> 04:32.171
Ooh! Oh! Ow!

04:32.238 --> 04:35.308
Don't forget the ice cubes,
Captain!

04:35.375 --> 04:37.143
[techno music plays]

04:37.210 --> 04:39.545
{\an1}[sniffing]
Man, you guys are ripe.

04:39.612 --> 04:41.881
We're never going to score
any chicks with that smell.

04:41.948 --> 04:43.683
{\an1}Here, try this cologne.
[spraying]

04:43.750 --> 04:44.917
Especially you, Rooter.

04:44.984 --> 04:45.952
{\an1}You're the rawest
of the bunch.

04:46.019 --> 04:46.953
Oi.

04:47.020 --> 04:48.121
So I told Tammy,

04:48.187 --> 04:49.589
{\an1}"Girl, he's just going
to use you."

04:49.656 --> 04:51.658
{\an1}But she's like:
"I don't want to hear it."

04:51.724 --> 04:54.227
{\an6}[sniffs]
Whoa, girl,
what's that smell?

04:55.561 --> 04:57.030
{\an1}Huh?

04:57.096 --> 04:58.264
♪ ♪

04:58.331 --> 05:00.033
Dang, you smell good.

05:00.099 --> 05:02.268
Yeah, you smell
real good.

05:02.335 --> 05:05.171
{\an1}All right, how about you
give me your digits?

05:05.238 --> 05:06.239
[all screaming]

05:06.305 --> 05:08.641
[muted screaming]

05:08.708 --> 05:10.677
[coughs, screams]

05:12.278 --> 05:13.713
[screaming]

05:13.780 --> 05:16.449
Ah! Ow!

05:19.619 --> 05:22.755
{\an1}Whatever! We weren't that
into you anyway.

05:22.822 --> 05:24.424
[all gasping]

05:24.490 --> 05:27.093
Pumpernickel root beer cake.

05:27.160 --> 05:28.861
Okay, we're fine.

05:28.928 --> 05:30.263
We just need to
check the map

05:30.329 --> 05:31.898
and see that we've been

05:31.964 --> 05:34.067
going the wrong direction!

05:34.133 --> 05:36.636
{\an3}2.5 miles in
the wrong direction.

05:36.703 --> 05:39.472
You knew? Why didn't you
say anything?

05:39.539 --> 05:41.841
Going 2.5 miles
the other way,

05:41.908 --> 05:43.176
far more challenging.

05:43.242 --> 05:45.611
Maybe there's another way
we can go.

05:45.678 --> 05:47.380
[groans]

05:47.447 --> 05:50.550
{\an3}Wow! How did you get
your eyeballs to do that?

05:50.616 --> 05:53.519
{\an3}[straining]
Ow!

05:53.586 --> 05:54.854
Okay, I've got it.

05:54.921 --> 05:56.456
We'll take a shortcut
across the lake.

05:56.522 --> 05:58.124
All we need is a boat.

05:58.191 --> 06:01.894
Okay, raise your hand
if you know how to build a boat.

06:03.629 --> 06:04.931
I don't know how
to build a boat,

06:04.997 --> 06:06.532
but I'll do it anyway.

06:06.599 --> 06:09.335
First of all, we're going
to need, like, 300 trees.

06:09.402 --> 06:11.471
That seems like WAY too many.

06:11.537 --> 06:13.005
{\an3}Well, we got to make it
big enough

06:13.072 --> 06:14.707
to hold all the hotties!

06:14.774 --> 06:15.508
Hotties?

06:15.575 --> 06:17.310
Yeah, all the super hot

06:17.376 --> 06:18.311
ladies that
will be out there

06:18.377 --> 06:19.412
to see the comet.

06:19.479 --> 06:20.747
There won't be

06:20.813 --> 06:21.981
any ladies out there.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.117
- No ladies?
- Nope.

06:24.183 --> 06:25.318
[owl hooting]

06:25.384 --> 06:27.386
Peace! Technobear out!

06:27.453 --> 06:29.088
[techno music]

06:29.155 --> 06:30.623
Wait, where are you going?

06:30.690 --> 06:33.059
{\an3}Boys, I can help you
build a boat.

06:33.126 --> 06:35.094
{\an3}First, cut down
two trees.

06:35.161 --> 06:36.496
But we don't have a saw.

06:36.562 --> 06:37.897
Apple bacon saxophone.

06:37.964 --> 06:41.300
{\an1}Yeah, we can probably find
some fallen trees.

06:41.367 --> 06:42.902
You understand him?

06:42.969 --> 06:46.372
{\an1}I've never understood anybody
better in my whole life.

06:46.439 --> 06:47.373
Horsefly Monopoly.

06:47.440 --> 06:48.841
All right, and then we can

06:48.908 --> 06:51.177
{\an1}tie the trees together
with whatever we can find.

06:51.244 --> 06:53.546
Hydroelectric jellybean
lunar module.

06:53.613 --> 06:57.450
{\an1}Okay, you guys, I think
I know how to build a boat.

06:58.618 --> 07:01.888
{\an1}I think something
got lost in translation.

07:01.954 --> 07:03.189
Well, it's all we got.

07:03.256 --> 07:04.524
Everybody on the boat!

07:04.590 --> 07:05.992
Sorry, boys, I'm swimming.

07:06.058 --> 07:08.761
{\an1}It will be way harder
and also more refreshing.

07:08.828 --> 07:10.363
{\an1}Ya!
[splashing]

07:12.198 --> 07:14.300
- Sorry, dude.
- It's okay.

07:14.367 --> 07:15.868
The boat probably
couldn't have handled

07:15.935 --> 07:18.104
his muscle mass anyway.

07:18.171 --> 07:21.107
[all grunting]

07:21.174 --> 07:23.509
[creaking, splashing]

07:23.576 --> 07:26.145
- Oh, no!
- I'm making snow angels!

07:26.212 --> 07:28.014
Eeee...

07:28.080 --> 07:29.549
Dad!

07:29.615 --> 07:32.952
I'm too floaty!
My head's too floaty!

07:33.019 --> 07:34.821
[rumbling]

07:40.993 --> 07:43.162
[coughing, spitting]

07:43.229 --> 07:44.564
Dad, are you Okay?

07:44.630 --> 07:45.998
Hopscotch magnet burger.

07:46.065 --> 07:48.167
{\an3}That's the worst boat
I've ever seen.

07:48.234 --> 07:49.435
{\an3}You want to drown
yourselves,

07:49.502 --> 07:51.838
{\an3}you do it in someone
else's lake.

07:54.040 --> 07:55.808
We'll never make it now.

07:55.875 --> 07:58.945
{\an3}I'm sorry, Dad.
I tried.

07:59.011 --> 08:00.880
Butter spider boggle top.

08:00.947 --> 08:03.549
{\an3}He says,
"It's okay, Harvey.

08:03.616 --> 08:06.018
{\an3}We'll catch
the next one."

08:07.353 --> 08:10.189
25 years?

08:10.256 --> 08:12.558
{\an1}We finally did it,
Father.

08:12.625 --> 08:15.528
After 25 long years...

08:15.595 --> 08:20.299
{\an1}[coughing]
...the comet is almost here.

08:20.366 --> 08:21.634
[groans]

08:21.701 --> 08:23.402
{\an1}Oh, no!

08:23.469 --> 08:25.371
No, we're going to make it.

08:25.438 --> 08:26.873
We have to make it!

08:28.207 --> 08:30.243
[straining]

08:30.309 --> 08:32.010
- There!
- The canyon?

08:32.078 --> 08:33.479
No, there!

08:33.546 --> 08:34.679
[straining]

08:34.746 --> 08:36.215
A bridge!

08:36.282 --> 08:37.216
{\an1}That will take us
over the canyon

08:37.283 --> 08:38.650
and right into the field.

08:38.717 --> 08:40.318
We're gonna do this!

08:40.385 --> 08:41.953
[creaking]

08:42.020 --> 08:43.188
[cracking]

08:43.256 --> 08:45.725
{\an1}Foo, do you know how
to fix bridges?

08:45.791 --> 08:46.726
Nope.

08:46.792 --> 08:47.994
{\an1}Dang it.

08:48.060 --> 08:50.730
{\an1}We'll just have to find
another way across.

08:51.731 --> 08:54.133
[inspirational music]

08:54.200 --> 08:55.801
I've got an idea.

08:57.203 --> 08:59.372
[grunting]

08:59.438 --> 09:00.907
{\an3}Harvey, I just wanted
to say

09:00.973 --> 09:02.942
of all the plans
you've ever had

09:03.009 --> 09:04.277
this one is my favorite.

09:04.343 --> 09:05.945
Okay, Dad, here we go.

09:06.012 --> 09:08.080
One, two, three!

09:08.147 --> 09:13.085
[both screaming]

09:13.152 --> 09:14.253
Whoa!

09:14.320 --> 09:16.222
{\an1}Hey, that actually worked
pretty well.

09:16.289 --> 09:19.892
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

09:21.394 --> 09:23.896
Quick! Catch him
coming back!

09:23.963 --> 09:24.931
Oh!

09:24.997 --> 09:26.766
- Harvey, I caught him.
- Foo!

09:27.934 --> 09:29.669
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

09:29.735 --> 09:31.871
[yelling gibberish]

09:31.938 --> 09:34.273
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

09:34.340 --> 09:35.841
{\an1}[echoing]
Aah!

09:35.908 --> 09:36.842
[grunts]

09:36.909 --> 09:38.177
Foo!

09:38.244 --> 09:39.512
I fell into a bush.

09:39.578 --> 09:41.981
{\an1}It's actually
pretty comfortable.

09:42.048 --> 09:43.449
Hoo!

09:46.519 --> 09:48.521
Oh, man, it's almost here.

09:48.587 --> 09:50.089
Dad, the comet's coming.

09:50.156 --> 09:51.924
{\an4}[grunts]
We've got to get
to the field.

09:51.991 --> 09:54.560
{\an1}Okay, Okay, Okay, I got it,
I got it.

09:54.627 --> 09:57.163
{\an1}[grunting]
Come on!

09:57.229 --> 09:59.265
We're so close!

09:59.332 --> 10:01.000
Huckleberry ginger grass.

10:01.067 --> 10:03.502
{\an3}I don't understand you,
Dad.

10:03.569 --> 10:06.539
{\an1}He said, "You can't do it
by yourself."

10:06.605 --> 10:08.341
Foo! You made it!

10:08.407 --> 10:09.442
{\an1}I made it!

10:09.508 --> 10:10.710
{\an3}Can you help me
with my dad?

10:10.776 --> 10:12.178
{\an1}Okay.

10:12.244 --> 10:13.546
[both grunting]

10:13.612 --> 10:15.314
He's pretty heavy.

10:15.381 --> 10:17.383
Looks like you two
could use a hand.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.018
- Rooter!
- Yep.

10:19.085 --> 10:20.853
And look who I found.

10:20.920 --> 10:22.822
- Techno Bear?
- I couldn't leave my bros

10:22.888 --> 10:25.858
out here alone, even if
there ain't no hotties.

10:25.925 --> 10:27.393
[grunting]

10:27.460 --> 10:28.627
Thank goodness.

10:28.694 --> 10:29.829
I've been walking
through these bushes

10:29.895 --> 10:30.896
over an hour.

10:30.963 --> 10:31.831
Oh, hey, Harvey.

10:31.897 --> 10:33.299
Everyone, quick,
grab my dad.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.901
[all breathing heavily]

10:35.968 --> 10:38.704
{\an1}Just a little bit closer,
guys!

10:38.771 --> 10:39.905
Wow!

10:41.407 --> 10:43.242
Quick, set him down here.

10:43.309 --> 10:44.410
[thud]
Whoops.

10:44.477 --> 10:46.779
Oh, huh? Where am I?

10:46.846 --> 10:48.881
Dad, it's the comet.

10:48.948 --> 10:50.983
Well, would you
look at that.

10:51.050 --> 10:54.520
[triumphant music]

10:54.587 --> 10:58.324
♪ ♪

10:58.391 --> 11:00.726
{\an1}Son, I don't remember
hiking here.

11:00.793 --> 11:02.128
But this is amazing.

11:02.194 --> 11:04.063
{\an1}I almost forgot.
Here, Dad.

11:04.130 --> 11:06.198
[laughs]
25 years.

11:06.265 --> 11:08.501
You know, I think it's
even better this time.

11:11.103 --> 11:13.839
{\an1}Harvey, have you seen
my pants anywhere?

11:16.776 --> 11:18.077
How nice.

11:18.144 --> 11:19.912
{\an3}We have the whole house
to ourselves, Fee.

11:19.979 --> 11:22.648
You making another cozy
for the egg, Mrs. Beaks?

11:22.715 --> 11:25.418
{\an3}Oh, yeah. You can never have
too many egg cozies.

11:25.484 --> 11:26.685
What you got there?

11:26.752 --> 11:27.853
I don't know.

11:27.920 --> 11:29.522
{\an1}I think it's going
to be a hat

11:29.588 --> 11:31.624
or maybe a boat sail.

11:31.690 --> 11:34.460
{\an3}You know, it's been
about 25 years

11:34.527 --> 11:36.062
since the comet came by.

11:36.128 --> 11:37.797
{\an3}The boys are probably
having fun

11:37.863 --> 11:39.598
{\an3}camping
out there tonight.

11:39.665 --> 11:43.436
{\an1}Yep, and we're just in here
being boring.

11:43.502 --> 11:47.840
{\an3}Well, I don't know
if I'd say it's boring.

11:47.907 --> 11:50.342
{\an3}You know, it doesn't have
to be a boring night.

11:50.409 --> 11:52.144
I mean, I'm not boring.

11:52.211 --> 11:55.114
{\an3}The stories
I could tell you.

11:57.716 --> 12:01.087
{\an3}My friends and I used to
paint the town red.

12:01.153 --> 12:04.223
{\an3}[gasps]
Okay, would a boring person

12:04.290 --> 12:06.225
{\an3}wear these?

12:06.292 --> 12:09.095
My sweet tiny pants!

12:09.161 --> 12:12.698
{\an3}[straining]

12:12.765 --> 12:15.501
{\an1}Mrs. Beaks,
these are awesome!

12:15.568 --> 12:17.236
Look at your hair. What?

12:17.303 --> 12:20.773
{\an1}You rode a moped?
Is that a flare gun?

12:20.840 --> 12:21.774
This must be you
and your friends

12:21.841 --> 12:23.576
on the night of the comet.

12:23.642 --> 12:25.211
Oh, let me see.

12:25.277 --> 12:26.512
Ha! Look at us!

12:26.579 --> 12:29.415
{\an1}Did you all really
get tattoos?

12:29.482 --> 12:30.850
Oh, ha! No.

12:30.916 --> 12:32.551
We just drew those on.

12:32.618 --> 12:34.687
We thought we were so cool.

12:34.753 --> 12:37.289
{\an1}I didn't know you had
this wild side.

12:37.356 --> 12:39.925
Fee, I think we're
pretty alike.

12:39.992 --> 12:41.894
We both like burning trash?

12:41.961 --> 12:43.596
{\an3}You know what?
Forget knitting tonight.

12:43.662 --> 12:47.433
{\an3}Let's go out there
and kick this town's butt!

12:50.236 --> 12:51.971
Oh...

12:52.037 --> 12:54.974
♪ ♪

13:01.814 --> 13:03.282
[doorbell rings]

13:03.349 --> 13:05.818
{\an3}Thanks for babysitting
the egg, Jeremy.

13:05.885 --> 13:07.786
Oh, yeah, it's my pleasure.

13:07.853 --> 13:09.555
{\an1}Whoop!
[splattering]

13:09.622 --> 13:12.925
Okay, let's go, Fee.

13:12.992 --> 13:16.362
{\an1}[kissing sound]
Coming, Mrs. Beaks.

13:16.428 --> 13:17.897
Ah, Okay, baby.

13:17.963 --> 13:20.699
Let's just go read
some bedtime stori--

13:20.766 --> 13:22.501
Oop!
[glass shatters]

13:22.568 --> 13:23.969
So, what should we do first?

13:24.036 --> 13:25.504
Build a fire pit?

13:25.571 --> 13:26.906
Last comet night started

13:26.972 --> 13:29.708
{\an1}with us getting
all the girls together.

13:29.775 --> 13:32.311
{\an1}Fee? Fee?!

13:32.378 --> 13:37.583
[shuffling, clatter]

13:37.650 --> 13:40.452
Okay, I got the girls
together.

13:40.519 --> 13:42.188
[all muttering]

13:42.254 --> 13:44.924
{\an1}Okay, girls, I want you
to hear me out.

13:44.990 --> 13:47.293
{\an1}How about instead of
having another

13:47.359 --> 13:49.595
boring, ordinary night,

13:49.662 --> 13:51.197
we put our heads together

13:51.263 --> 13:55.267
{\an1}and we make this
the craziest night of the comet

13:55.334 --> 13:58.003
anyone has ever seen!

13:58.070 --> 14:00.372
{\an1}But...but I'm supposed
to be at home

14:00.439 --> 14:01.907
practicing my oboe.

14:01.974 --> 14:05.311
{\an1}Mom says it's against
the rules to skip practice.

14:05.377 --> 14:07.580
Claire, on comet night...

14:07.646 --> 14:09.682
there are no rules!

14:09.748 --> 14:13.152
I've waited for this day
to come.

14:13.219 --> 14:14.687
Hold on--let me check
my schedule first.

14:14.753 --> 14:16.755
[scribbling]

14:16.822 --> 14:17.923
Whatever!

14:17.990 --> 14:18.958
My friends and I

14:19.024 --> 14:21.327
would wear these scrunchies

14:21.393 --> 14:22.728
on all of our adventures.

14:22.795 --> 14:25.030
Okay, I want all of us
to hold hands

14:25.097 --> 14:27.866
while I sing a song
I wrote about sisterhood.

14:27.933 --> 14:29.001
I wrote this
in a language

14:29.068 --> 14:30.769
I learned in a dream.

14:30.836 --> 14:35.040
♪ Ooh la gooboo
la ma pujja ma ♪

14:35.107 --> 14:39.712
♪ Sha sisters tiji
shaaaa ♪

14:39.778 --> 14:41.313
I'm hungry!

14:41.380 --> 14:42.715
[crickets chirping]

14:42.781 --> 14:44.516
And here's your milkshake.

14:44.583 --> 14:48.287
And one milkshake
with all the straws.

14:48.354 --> 14:51.557
Gimme!
[slurping]

14:51.624 --> 14:52.825
Excuse me, sir,

14:52.891 --> 14:56.662
{\an1}I'll take 20 orders
of sauerkraut...

14:56.729 --> 14:57.763
[all gasp]

14:57.830 --> 15:00.466
...and send it
to that table.

15:00.532 --> 15:01.533
[all gasp]

15:01.600 --> 15:03.836
{\an1}And I want you to deliver
this note.

15:03.902 --> 15:06.672
{\an1}"Your weird head
makes my heart soar.

15:06.739 --> 15:07.873
"I'm in love with you.

15:07.940 --> 15:10.776
{\an1}Let's have
weird-headed babies."

15:10.843 --> 15:13.045
You're pranking that table?

15:13.112 --> 15:14.680
Adults can't do that!

15:14.747 --> 15:15.948
Cool adults can.

15:16.015 --> 15:17.149
That's right.

15:17.216 --> 15:18.751
[gasping]

15:18.817 --> 15:20.819
So much sauerkraut.

15:20.886 --> 15:21.954
{\an3}[groaning]

15:22.021 --> 15:24.423
This is really happening!

15:24.490 --> 15:26.091
Ah, Gerald.

15:26.158 --> 15:28.327
{\an1}Is this how you
really feel?

15:28.394 --> 15:30.729
{\an3}I don't know what
you're talking about.

15:30.796 --> 15:32.965
Gerald, come here, you.

15:33.032 --> 15:34.700
[kissing sounds]

15:34.767 --> 15:38.003
Comet night is back!

15:38.070 --> 15:40.139
Ah! Ah!
Don't worry, little egg.

15:40.205 --> 15:42.274
I'll get you down.

15:42.341 --> 15:44.343
Just fall on top
of the pillows.

15:44.410 --> 15:46.011
Hold tight, little egg,
I'm just gonna--

15:46.078 --> 15:48.147
Ah! Ah! Where'd you go?

15:48.213 --> 15:50.749
Did you hatch and fly away?

15:50.816 --> 15:52.217
Little egg!

15:52.284 --> 15:55.421
No!

15:55.487 --> 15:59.058
{\an4}(Randl)
Aren't you all the wrong age
to be going to a prom?

15:59.124 --> 16:00.559
{\an3}We want to rent
prom dresses

16:00.626 --> 16:02.094
for our own cool prom.

16:02.161 --> 16:03.862
{\an3}It's a comet night
thing,

16:03.929 --> 16:05.531
{\an3}pretty different,
I know.

16:05.597 --> 16:08.634
{\an1}Randl, remember I saved
all those dresses

16:08.701 --> 16:10.035
for your future wife,

16:10.102 --> 16:11.804
{\an1}But then you never
got married.

16:11.870 --> 16:13.372
Mom, go to sleep!

16:14.540 --> 16:16.342
(all)
Wow!

16:16.408 --> 16:19.411
[harp music]

16:19.478 --> 16:22.648
Um, we're going to
need a boom box.

16:22.715 --> 16:24.216
[rock music]

16:24.283 --> 16:27.453
[giggling]

16:27.519 --> 16:28.620
Nobody touch
that one!

16:28.687 --> 16:30.456
I want to try it!

16:30.522 --> 16:33.492
I'm invincible.

16:33.559 --> 16:34.860
Ah! Ah!

16:34.927 --> 16:36.528
And then Archibald
proposed to me,

16:36.595 --> 16:39.832
but I told him I don't
kiss on the fifth date.

16:39.898 --> 16:42.000
{\an3}Oh, don't we look
amazing!

16:42.067 --> 16:44.536
I bet I look better
in this than Harvey would.

16:44.603 --> 16:45.938
[both laugh]

16:46.004 --> 16:48.307
{\an3}Actually, Harvey would
look pretty great in this.

16:48.374 --> 16:49.341
Yeah.

16:49.408 --> 16:51.009
[static, sizzle]

16:51.076 --> 16:53.212
Hey, you've got
to pay for that.

16:53.278 --> 16:54.813
But we didn't touch it.

16:54.880 --> 16:57.015
Besides, all this music
is so obvious.

16:57.082 --> 16:59.752
Don't you have anything
cool and obscure?

16:59.818 --> 17:01.954
Uh, I don't even--
I don't--

17:02.020 --> 17:03.288
You know what?

17:03.355 --> 17:05.590
I have records no one
has ever heard before.

17:05.656 --> 17:07.092
Just wait there.

17:07.159 --> 17:08.926
Okay, let's go.

17:08.993 --> 17:10.729
You too,
Randl's mom.

17:10.796 --> 17:12.297
And that's the night
I realized

17:12.364 --> 17:14.900
I'm impervious to fire.

17:14.967 --> 17:17.236
[all laughing]

17:17.301 --> 17:19.304
{\an3}This is pretty crazy,
huh, Fee?

17:19.371 --> 17:20.506
{\an1}Uh, yeah.

17:20.571 --> 17:21.740
But, Mrs. Beaks,

17:21.807 --> 17:23.142
{\an1}are you sure
you're really cool

17:23.208 --> 17:24.410
with stealing like this?

17:24.476 --> 17:26.044
{\an3}We'll return the dresses
tomorrow.

17:26.111 --> 17:27.913
It's all in good fun.

17:27.980 --> 17:30.048
Um, Okay.

17:30.115 --> 17:32.184
Ah! Ah!
How did this happen?

17:32.251 --> 17:34.019
Stay away from us,
you bats!

17:34.086 --> 17:37.423
Aah! Aah! Aah! Aah!

17:37.489 --> 17:40.426
Okay, girls, I'm taking us
to my favorite place

17:40.492 --> 17:41.760
to let loose.

17:41.827 --> 17:43.128
[thump]

17:43.195 --> 17:45.264
Welcome to the coolest
roller skating rink

17:45.330 --> 17:47.032
in Littlebark Grove!

17:47.099 --> 17:48.901
[Muzak plays]

17:48.967 --> 17:51.670
This looks like
a nursing home.

17:51.737 --> 17:53.338
[arm creaking]

17:53.405 --> 17:56.208
Okay, maybe I haven't been here
in 25 years.

17:56.275 --> 17:58.377
Well, that was fun
while it lasted.

17:58.444 --> 17:59.978
I guess we better
head back home

18:00.045 --> 18:01.480
and get back to those
egg cozies,

18:01.547 --> 18:02.848
right Mrs. Beaks?

18:02.915 --> 18:07.286
[Muzak continues]

18:07.352 --> 18:10.189
No, no, no, no!
We're doing this!

18:10.255 --> 18:12.724
Girls, let's pump up the jams!

18:12.791 --> 18:14.326
Oi! Here?

18:14.393 --> 18:17.596
Yeah, come on, girls.
Go be crazy.

18:17.663 --> 18:19.832
{\an3}Remember,
night of the comet.

18:19.898 --> 18:21.400
{\an3}No rules!

18:22.701 --> 18:24.436
[growls]

18:24.503 --> 18:26.805
{\an1}Ma'am? Visiting hours
are over.

18:26.872 --> 18:27.940
Whatever!

18:28.006 --> 18:31.410
The party hour's
just started!

18:31.477 --> 18:34.146
[laughing]

18:34.213 --> 18:37.616
I keep...
I want...

18:37.683 --> 18:38.884
[mumbling]

18:38.951 --> 18:41.053
Yeah. Whoo.

18:41.119 --> 18:43.021
Oh dear, I better call
for help.

18:43.088 --> 18:44.289
Hello, police?

18:44.356 --> 18:46.992
{\an1}Evil, beware.
Officer Fred is here

18:47.059 --> 18:49.361
{\an1}to kick wickedness
in the bootie.

18:49.428 --> 18:51.363
- Where?
- Here. Down here.

18:51.430 --> 18:53.866
{\an3}Oh, thank gosh you're here,
Officer Fred.

18:53.932 --> 18:57.069
{\an1}Let me just assess
the situation.

18:57.135 --> 18:58.937
{\an1}You there!
Drop that weapon!

18:59.004 --> 19:00.939
- Aba-zap!
- [whimpering]

19:01.006 --> 19:02.508
You! Stop running!

19:02.574 --> 19:04.309
{\an1}Ba-zang!

19:04.376 --> 19:07.079
{\an5}[stammering]
No, we called you
because of them.

19:07.145 --> 19:09.815
[laughing, yelling]

19:09.882 --> 19:11.149
What? Police?

19:11.216 --> 19:13.485
I'm not going back
into lockup.

19:13.552 --> 19:14.686
I did my time.

19:14.753 --> 19:15.854
Let's get out of here.

19:15.921 --> 19:17.656
[giggling]

19:17.723 --> 19:19.324
Fee, are you having fun?

19:19.391 --> 19:21.527
I think I'm going
to throw up!

19:21.593 --> 19:23.662
Me too!
[laughs]

19:23.729 --> 19:25.464
Ow!
[sizzling]

19:25.531 --> 19:29.801
{\an1}Ba-zow! Ba-zap! Ba-zang!
Ba-zoi! Ba-zow!

19:29.868 --> 19:31.003
Is this--ow!

19:31.069 --> 19:32.671
Really necessary?

19:32.738 --> 19:33.805
Ow!

19:33.872 --> 19:35.974
Ba-zang! Ba-zow! Ba-zang!

19:36.041 --> 19:37.576
[cell doors clanking]

19:37.643 --> 19:41.380
Miriam, I just--
you stole my stuff.

19:41.446 --> 19:42.981
But you lost my mother.

19:43.048 --> 19:44.182
So I guess we're even.

19:44.249 --> 19:46.652
Ha, look at these party poopers.

19:46.718 --> 19:48.287
Am I right, Fee?

19:48.353 --> 19:49.321
I don't know.

19:49.388 --> 19:51.356
That wasn't really fun.

19:51.423 --> 19:53.792
I'm kind of glad
we're in prison right now.

19:53.859 --> 19:56.762
{\an1}What? But I thought you were
all about the whoo

19:56.828 --> 19:59.231
and the haah and the rrr!

19:59.298 --> 20:01.667
Yeah, I like that stuff.

20:01.733 --> 20:04.369
But I also like knitting
cozies with you.

20:04.436 --> 20:05.938
You said that was boring.

20:06.004 --> 20:09.408
Yeah, you know, boring's
not always a bad thing.

20:11.376 --> 20:13.545
{\an3}Sometimes, I'm a little
jealous of Harvey.

20:13.612 --> 20:15.280
{\an3}He gets to have fun
with Foo and me

20:15.347 --> 20:17.683
{\an3}and then come home
and hang out with you guys.

20:17.749 --> 20:21.286
{\an3}I guess I just want that
sometimes too.

20:21.353 --> 20:24.523
{\an1}Remember that time we ate
peanut butter off the floor?

20:24.590 --> 20:26.024
{\an3}And then we both got
tummy aches

20:26.091 --> 20:28.193
{\an3}and couldn't get up
for an hour.

20:28.260 --> 20:29.695
Or the time we switched around

20:29.761 --> 20:31.163
all of Irving's plants

20:31.229 --> 20:33.899
{\an1}and it took him weeks
before he figured it out.

20:33.966 --> 20:35.801
Or the time we dropped
Harvey's toothbrush

20:35.867 --> 20:37.869
in the toilet
and didn't tell him.

20:37.936 --> 20:39.304
- What?
- Never mind.

20:39.371 --> 20:41.873
[both laugh]

20:41.940 --> 20:43.775
I'm having fun now.

20:43.842 --> 20:45.611
Yeah, me too.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.850
Oh, it's the comet!

20:51.917 --> 20:57.823
[uplifting music]

20:57.889 --> 21:02.861
♪ ♪

21:02.928 --> 21:04.529
Eh, seen it.

21:15.807 --> 21:17.509
{\an3}Okay, it doesn't have
to be

21:17.576 --> 21:19.511
a totally normal night.

21:22.848 --> 21:24.683
[clang]

21:24.750 --> 21:27.319
[both laughing]

21:29.221 --> 21:31.657
{\an1}I hope the egg wasn't
too much trouble.

21:31.723 --> 21:33.025
We're back!

21:33.091 --> 21:34.259
[both gasp]

21:34.326 --> 21:36.795
Oh, welcome back.

21:36.862 --> 21:38.063
Egg is just fine.

21:38.130 --> 21:41.199
We're enjoying a nice,
quiet night. Ho ho.

21:41.266 --> 21:42.834
Did you guys have
a good time?

21:42.901 --> 21:46.304
{\an1}Yeah, but I think we're
just going to take it easy now.

21:46.371 --> 21:49.508
[rock music]

21:49.574 --> 21:51.009
♪ ♪

21:51.076 --> 21:53.512
{\an1}[giggling]

21:53.578 --> 21:57.683
Am we dreaming
or is this reality?

21:57.749 --> 22:00.385
♪ ♪
